body_html:
@Derekkk
Only x86_64 TensorFlow native library binaries are uploaded to Maven. (See libtensorflow_jni artifact)
So need 64-bit (x86_64) version of JVM to run TensorFlow. Not 32-bit (x86).
If that is not possible you could try compiling your own 32-bit TensorFlow binary for Windows.

body:
@Derekkk 
Only x86_64 TensorFlow native library binaries are uploaded to Maven. (See `libtensorflow_jni` artifact)
So need 64-bit (x86_64) version of JVM to run TensorFlow. Not 32-bit (x86). 
If that is not possible you could try compiling your own 32-bit TensorFlow binary for Windows.
